social_posts.post_text: Merry Christmas from my little family to yours!

Cheers to another great time shooting the Sundance Film Festival! A big thank you to all of the editors, photographers, and support team that made everything run smoothly. And thanks to Sony Alpha for loaning me the brand new 20-70mm to test out (it never left my camera!).

#sonyalpha #sonya7iv #eventphotography #eventphotographer #sundance2023

New work for the new Seattle post of Sushi By Scratch in downtown Seattle. The 17-course omakase menu was my favorite sushi meal I’ve had in town.

#sushi #seattlefoodie #seattlefoodies #seattlerestaurants #pnwfood #seattleeats
A day late, but yesterday was our ELEVEN year anniversary. Suffice to say life looks pretty different these days 😅 These were some of our engagement photos taken by @jonathangipaya.

New photo work of the catering menu at Jackalope Tex Mex and Cantina, one of my favorite restaurants in South Seattle. Shot entirely with the new Rotolight AEOS 2 Pro and NEO 3 Pro — game changing continuous LED lights for photo or video.

It’s not often I get the chance to push myself creatively, but that’s what I did every day during #SonyKandoTrip. From trying different photography styles, to working with new to me pieces of gear, to striking up conversations with complete strangers and artists and creators who I’ve admired for years, I never knew a trip like this could be so fulfilling and inspiring. Thank you @sonyalpha and @sonyelectronics for inviting me to be apart of such an amazing community. #sonypartner 

Btw most of these photos (including the blue moon) were shot on the Sony RX100 VII point and shoot, because I love pushing tiny cameras to their limits 📸

No. But it’s very water resistant with an IP68 rating, meaning it can survive up to 1 meter (3.3 feet) for 30 minutes.
